1
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:19,959
This madder you use for dyeing,

2
00:01:20,319 --> 00:01:22,000
do you just pick it wherever you go?

3
00:01:22,400 --> 00:01:22,840
Yeah.

4
00:01:23,840 --> 00:01:25,159
We need to protect the ecosystem, right?

5
00:01:25,560 --> 00:01:27,120
I can't strip one spot bare.

6
00:01:27,480 --> 00:01:29,040
So I picked some from the sunny side,

7
00:01:29,280 --> 00:01:30,280
some from the shady slope,

8
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:31,799
and some from along the creek.

9
00:01:33,280 --> 00:01:34,359
That was my oversight.

10
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:35,760
That's exactly where the problem is.

11
00:01:36,319 --> 00:01:37,799
The sunlight and moisture are different.

12
00:01:37,959 --> 00:01:39,760
The pH values in this batch are clashing.

13
00:01:40,079 --> 00:01:41,280
So the colors came out wrong.

14
00:01:43,079 --> 00:01:43,599
You mean,

15
00:01:44,040 --> 00:01:45,879
some of the rice in the pot is raw,

16
00:01:45,879 --> 00:01:47,040
some is mushy,

17
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:48,120
and they just can't cook together.

18
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:51,560
Then I'll pick more on the back hill now.

19
00:01:51,959 --> 00:01:52,760
Is there still time?

20
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:56,040
To pick out uniform madder,

21
00:01:56,439 --> 00:01:57,359
it'll take at least half a month.

22
00:01:57,920 --> 00:01:58,640
Half a month?

23
00:01:59,359 --> 00:02:00,159
That won't work.

24
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:02,359
I just put the announcement out.

25
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:03,920
This would ruin our reputation.

26
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:09,280
What if...

27
00:02:10,039 --> 00:02:11,080
I'm just saying, what if...

28
00:02:11,159 --> 00:02:12,240
as a quick fix,

29
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:15,039
we add just a tiny bit of chemical dye?

30
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:18,520
Chemical dye tech is great these days.

31
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:19,840
It meets eco-friendly standards.

32
00:02:20,039 --> 00:02:20,840
And the colors are vibrant.

33
00:02:21,479 --> 00:02:22,759
We just add a tiny bit as a base,

34
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:24,759
then top it off with plant dyeing.

35
00:02:25,039 --> 00:02:26,159
No one would ever notice.

36
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:29,800
Do you know what the sign

37
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:30,759
outside my door says?

38
00:02:32,159 --> 00:02:33,680
Intangible Cultural Heritage Workshop.

39
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:35,000
That's right.

40
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:36,800
My craft

41
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:38,560
is plant dyeing from our ancestors.

42
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:40,479
Every single thread

43
00:02:41,080 --> 00:02:42,759
goes through more than a dozen steps.

44
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,759
It must soak up the soul of the plants.

45
00:02:45,639 --> 00:02:46,759
As long as it comes from my hands,

46
00:02:47,159 --> 00:02:48,960
and bears the Peach Blossom Village brand,

47
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:50,719
it must be done with plant dyeing.

48
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:53,319
But the thing is, we're gonna lose money.

49
00:02:53,639 --> 00:02:54,879
Our credibility will be ruined.

50
00:02:56,599 --> 00:02:58,919
I think using chemical dye

51
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:00,840
is what would truly ruin our reputation.

52
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:06,039
Everyone, don't panic.

53
00:03:06,879 --> 00:03:07,759
I think

54
00:03:08,439 --> 00:03:09,680
we can always find a way.

55
00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:10,919
I was wondering,

56
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:12,639
could we use a different plant?

57
00:03:13,240 --> 00:03:14,039
A different plant?

58
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:17,479
Something with a stronger base.

59
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:19,199
Tibetan Madder.

60
00:03:19,439 --> 00:03:21,319
Tibetan Madder's red pigment is so strong

61
00:03:21,479 --> 00:03:22,560
that it can completely overpower

62
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:24,240
the uneven acidity of regular madder.

63
00:03:24,919 --> 00:03:26,000
So where do we find this plant?

64
00:03:26,159 --> 00:03:27,000
I'll go get some right now.

65
00:03:28,319 --> 00:03:28,919
We have to go into the mountains.

66
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:32,879
I saw it near Black Eagle Beak before.

67
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:34,759
Cattle and sheep don't like to eat it.

68
00:03:34,879 --> 00:03:35,479
Too bitter for them.

69
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:38,199
Black Eagle Beak is deep in the canyon.

70
00:03:38,479 --> 00:03:39,560
The terrain is really tough.

71
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:40,639
Don't worry.

72
00:03:41,159 --> 00:03:42,039
Bro Jimei and I went there before

73
00:03:42,039 --> 00:03:43,240
when we were looking for ingredients.

74
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:46,800
Medok has been there too.

75
00:03:47,719 --> 00:03:48,120
Here's the plan.

76
00:03:48,439 --> 00:03:50,639
Let's go together and gather all we can.

77
00:03:51,919 --> 00:03:53,199
Then please, be safe out there.

78
00:03:53,599 --> 00:03:55,280
You must be back before dark.

79
00:03:56,199 --> 00:03:56,639
Okay.

80
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:05,280
And take this.

81
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:06,680
Here.

82
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:11,599
I'm going too.

83
00:04:12,599 --> 00:04:13,280
Nana, you...

84
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:14,759
You're being ridiculous.

85
00:04:14,759 --> 00:04:15,879
That's Black Eagle Beak.

86
00:04:15,919 --> 00:04:16,720
There aren't even any roads.

87
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:18,639
A city kid like you going out there?

88
00:04:18,639 --> 00:04:19,680
You'd just slow us down.

89
00:04:19,959 --> 00:04:21,040
I'm not going to slow you down.

90
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:24,879
I have a Red Cross first aid certificate.

91
00:04:25,399 --> 00:04:26,519
I brought a full set of wound care meds

92
00:04:26,759 --> 00:04:27,600
and anti-allergy medication.

93
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:29,839
If anything happens out there,

94
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,680
I mean, just in case,

95
00:04:33,240 --> 00:04:34,000
I'd be more useful than any of you.

96
00:04:35,279 --> 00:04:36,000
Besides,

97
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:38,279
I just want to see for myself

98
00:04:40,079 --> 00:04:41,800
what kind of mountain it really is

99
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:44,639
that makes someone willingly stay here.

100
00:05:08,519 --> 00:05:10,079
Don't run around in the woods.

101
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:10,959
Stay safe.

102
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:12,680
I promise I'll listen.

103
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:27,839
It's okay, it's okay.

104
00:05:42,759 --> 00:05:44,079
It was just fine a moment ago.

105
00:05:44,519 --> 00:05:45,759
How did it start raining so suddenly?

106
00:05:47,079 --> 00:05:48,000
That's just how it is in the mountains.

107
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:48,959
You'll get used to it.

108
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:52,000
Careful, careful.

109
00:06:11,759 --> 00:06:12,120
Tashi.

110
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:27,519
The pH value...

111
00:06:27,519 --> 00:06:28,079
is 5.5.

112
00:06:28,519 --> 00:06:30,199
The ground temp is three degrees lower.

113
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:40,639
The humus layer is thick enough.

114
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:43,959
And there's moisture from underground currents.

115
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:45,360
All the data matches up.

116
00:06:45,959 --> 00:06:46,920
You mean...

117
00:06:47,399 --> 00:06:48,279
it's somewhere around here?

118
00:06:49,639 --> 00:06:50,279
It's definitely here.

119
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:51,360
And it's a large cluster.

120
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:55,199
This area is too big.

121
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:56,639
Let's split up.

122
00:06:58,560 --> 00:06:59,480
I'll go with Jimei.

123
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:02,920
In case something happens,

124
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:04,759
I've got the first-aid kit.

125
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:09,560
Bro Jimei.

126
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:10,839
Sure.

127
00:07:11,879 --> 00:07:12,560
You guys be careful.

128
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:13,879
Stay in touch.

129
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:16,160
You stay safe too.

130
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:16,959
Okay, you too.

131
00:07:17,399 --> 00:07:18,360
Keep in touch!

132
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:19,279
Got it, we'll stay in touch.

133
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:24,160
Tell me,

134
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:27,040
Why did Nana pair up with Bro Jimei?

135
00:07:29,439 --> 00:07:30,240
What do you think?

136
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:32,240
I'm asking because I don't know.

137
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:35,639
She's his daughter.

138
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:36,839
I know that.

139
00:07:37,399 --> 00:07:38,600
But doesn't she hate him?

140
00:07:39,519 --> 00:07:41,000
Hate is also a form of caring.

141
00:07:51,319 --> 00:07:51,920
Be careful!

142
00:07:54,839 --> 00:07:55,519
Watch out.

143
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:11,959
Why did you leave back then?

144
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:16,480
Why did you leave without a word?

145
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:20,160
Does dodging debt justify disappearing?

146
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:21,920
I need answers today.

147
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:27,279
Back in those years,

148
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:28,720
things were going too smoothly.

149
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:31,240
The restaurant was thriving.

150
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:33,519
We had money saved up.

151
00:08:35,360 --> 00:08:37,559
Someone offered me an investment.

152
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:40,279
And then?

153
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,360
Then I lost it all.

154
00:08:43,399 --> 00:08:44,240
Overnight,

155
00:08:45,519 --> 00:08:46,480
everything was gone.

156
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:49,480
Creditors were after me everywhere.

157
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:51,600
They called and threatened me.

158
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:54,600
Then why didn't you tell us?

159
00:08:59,000 --> 00:08:59,679
Back then,

160
00:09:01,039 --> 00:09:02,320
I had nightmares every night.

161
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:05,360
I dreamed creditors came to our door.

162
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:07,200
You were kneeling in the corner, crying.

163
00:09:07,879 --> 00:09:08,519
Your mom

164
00:09:09,639 --> 00:09:10,559
was on her knees, begging them.

165
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:13,600
Later, I thought it through.

166
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:16,039
Only by leaving

167
00:09:16,879 --> 00:09:18,120
could I keep you out of it.

168
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:21,120
Before I left,

169
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:23,639
I signed the divorce papers.

170
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:25,159
and left them with a lawyer.

171
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:27,279
Better I bear it alone

172
00:09:28,159 --> 00:09:29,320
than drag you all down with me.

173
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:33,360
If I could bear it, I would.

174
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:35,120
And if I couldn't,

175
00:09:36,799 --> 00:09:37,360
it wouldn't matter.

176
00:09:37,879 --> 00:09:39,480
What do you mean it wouldn't matter?

177
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:42,879
Were you...

178
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:44,960
Were you thinking...

179
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:48,799
Were you thinking of killing yourself?

180
00:09:50,559 --> 00:09:51,879
Later, I found a place.

181
00:09:53,159 --> 00:09:54,240
A very high place.

182
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:56,200
I stood there,

183
00:09:58,320 --> 00:09:59,519
and one step forward

184
00:10:02,159 --> 00:10:03,559
would end it all.

185
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:07,200
But the weather was beautiful that day.

186
00:10:08,039 --> 00:10:08,840
I stood there,

187
00:10:09,639 --> 00:10:10,840
looking at Mount Namcha Barwa.

188
00:10:12,399 --> 00:10:14,000
The snow was white, the sky was blue.

189
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:16,120
The mountain just stood there in silence,

190
00:10:17,039 --> 00:10:18,320
as if it had something to tell me.

191
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:20,759
Suddenly, I didn't want to die anymore.

192
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:22,519
I thought,

193
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:24,919
It's stood there for thousands of years.

194
00:10:25,360 --> 00:10:26,960
Wind and rain can't bring it down.

195
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:28,360
So why should I fall?

196
00:10:30,279 --> 00:10:30,879
Then...

197
00:10:32,279 --> 00:10:33,440
Didn't you miss us?

198
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:36,120
Of course I did.

199
00:10:37,440 --> 00:10:38,440
Every single day.

200
00:10:40,159 --> 00:10:41,879
Then why didn't you come see us?

201
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:43,840
I didn't dare go back.

202
00:10:45,279 --> 00:10:46,480
At first, I didn't dare.

203
00:10:47,240 --> 00:10:48,159
Then as time passed,

204
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:52,679
I just didn't know how to face you.
